oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Dr. W. Boyce and nurses
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Dr. W. Boyce and his nurses standing in front of Boyce Medical Clinic.

William Earl Boyce established his medical practice in 1939 and retired in 1957. Throughout the 1940s, Dr. Boyce's clinic was the only one available in the Hohenwald area; people from all over Lewis County would travel to receive medical treatment.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
